Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Located within a five minute drive of downtown Akron, and just a stone’s throw from Interstates 76/77 and State Route 8, The East End offers its residents, tenants, and visitors alike unprecedented access to Live/Work/Play opportunities within close proximity to each other. 

Once the campus of the historic Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company, the East End has been transformed for today’s needs.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The East End is a 1.4 million square foot mixed use redevelopment initiative that offers Akron’s newest and best “LIVE, WORK & PLAY” experience. In addition to the Residence Loft Apartments and Hilton Garden Inn Hotel, this exciting new community now also includes two concert/event venues, a fully managed sports complex and Class A Office space with an ultra modern lobby with first class amenities.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: The PNC Center Tower is the epicenter of the Akron CBD at the corner of Bowery and S. Main Street. Strategically located off the SR59 Corridor into Downtown Akron, this CBD site has an interior parking garage that allows for covered access to the office tower. Its 23 floors offer majestic views of the City and Cuyahoga Valley along with the newly landscape Cascade Plaza offering a park-like setting with green space and easy access to restaurants, services and the Towpath Trail.
